The Niryo Ned2 is a 6-axis collaborative robotic arm designed for educational purposes, vocational training, and research. It offers a versatile platform for learning and prototyping in robotics and automation. 
NIRYO

Key Features:

6 Degrees of Freedom (DOF): Enables complex movements and precise positioning, closely emulating industrial robots.

Open-Source Architecture: Built on ROS (Robot Operating System), Raspberry Pi, and Arduino, allowing for extensive customization and integration.

Multiple Programming Interfaces: Supports visual programming through Blockly-based Niryo Studio, as well as text-based coding in Python, C++, and MATLAB.

Educational Ecosystem: Compatible width various accessories like conveyor belts and vision kits, facilitating hands-on learning in Industry 4.0 scenarios.

User-Friendly Design: Features an aluminum structure for durability and precision, width a repeatability of approximately 0.5 mm. 
GENERATION ROBOTS

The Niryo Ned2 serves as an accessible tool for students and professionals to explore robotics, programming, and automation, bridging the gap between theoretical knowledge and practical application.
